analyze_rail(25.10)                                        analyze_rail(25.10)

Name
       analyze_rail - Runs rail analysis on a net or domain

Syntax
       analyze_rail

       [-help]

       [-type {domain | net}]

       [-output <directory_name>]

       <name>

       Runs  rail  analysis on a net or domain. This command must be specified
       after  defining  the  rail   analysis   mode   properties   using   the
       set_rail_analysis_mode command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each analyze_rail parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command man analyze_rail.

       <name> Specifies the name of the domain or net that you  want  to  ana-
              lyze.

       -output <directory_name>
              Specifies the name of the directory in which to store the output
              directories created during the analysis.

              Default: Current working directory.

       -type {domain | net}
              Specifies  whether  to run rail analysis on a domain or a net. A
              domain is a list of power or ground nets  to  analyze  together.
              See set_power_pads for more details.

              You can specify the variable "ALL" to analyze all domains.

Examples
              * The following command performs an analysis for the vdd net and
                places the results directories in the analysis_out directory:

                analyze_rail -type net -output analysis_out vdd

              * The  next  command performs rail analysis on TDSP power domain
                and writes the results in current working directory.

                analyze_rail -type domain -output ./ TDSP

              * The following command performs rail analysis on all power  do-
                mains and writes the results in the current working directory:

                analyze_rail -type domain ALL -output ./

Related Information
              * set_rail_analysis_mode

              * "Static  Power, IRdrop and EM Analysis" in the Voltus IC Power
                Integrity Solution User Guide

              * "Dynamic Power and IRDrop Analysis" in the Voltus IC Power In-
